package corejava;
public class Ginheritance {
	public int steps=4;
	public void block(){
	System.out.println("this block require 4 steps ,how many steps available now:"+steps);
	}	
public static class inheritance2 extends Ginheritance{
	public int steps1=4;
	public void block2(){
	System.out.println("this block require 8 steps so we can add from old class"+(steps1+steps));}	
public static void main(String[] args) {
	inheritance2 i=new inheritance2();
	i.block();
	i.block2();	
}		
}
}

/*

this program in inheritance ,we can use the date from old class with keyword of extends

 when we use extends we can able to use old class so that we can avoid program waste  
 
 type: 
 1)single inhrt
 2)multi level inhrt
 3)multiple inhrt(not support)
 
 
 
 */



